		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical History</head>
			
		<p>Adolphe Adam was a French composer.  He wrote primarily for the theatre, composing operas, ballets, light operas and vaudeville during his career.  He is best known for some of his ballets, such as <emph render="italic">Giselle</emph> and <emph render="italic">Le Corsaire</emph>.</p></bioghist>
		
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>The collection consists of a single original manuscript (two leaves, written on both sides)   for a song, in Adam's handwriting and with his signature at the top.  The words are in French.  The song is not identified.</p>
		</scopecontent>
		
